{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879062021,"sessionID":"ses_2855cccfcffeKWiqLygEoViRUd","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa401d1001X5KXKFjDUbKDpW","messageID":"msg_d7aa3f4a8001V1tBH7ahiW6FT7","sessionID":"ses_2855cccfcffeKWiqLygEoViRUd","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e2b269c202e64560845950afe642aeb7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement a dual-provider deployment system for the AgentCube CLI that enables AI agents to be deployed to either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service) or the AgentCube custom resource (AgentRuntime CR). This feature provides users with flexibility in deployment targets while maintaining a consistent CLI experience.\n6: \n7: ## Motivation\n8: \n9: Users have different infrastructure setups:\n10: - **Standard Kubernetes**: Teams with existing K8s clusters who want to deploy agents as standard Deployments and NodePort Services\n11: - **AgentCube CRD**: Teams using the AgentCube operator (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh) who benefit from specialized CRD features like session management, workload manager integration, and router-based invocation\n12: \n13: Supporting both deployment targets from a single CLI tool reduces operational complexity and enables gradual adoption of AgentCube-specific features.\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: ### In Scope\n18: \n19: | Component | Description |\n20: |-----------|-------------|\n21: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` class for standard K8s Deployment/Service |\n22: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` class for AgentRuntime CRD |\n23: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Provider selection logic in `publish` command |\n24: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | Provider-aware invocation routing |\n25: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Provider-specific status retrieval |\n26: | CLI commands | `--provider` flag for `publish`, `invoke`, `status` commands |\n27: \n28: ### Out of Scope\n29: \n30: - Cloud build mode implementation (future AR)\n31: - Helm chart generation\n32: - Multi-cluster deployment\n33: - GitOps integration\n34: \n35: ## Architecture\n36: \n37: ```\n38: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n39: │                      CLI (main.py)                          │\n40: │  pack │ build │ publish │ invoke │ status                  │\n41: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n42:                       │\n43:                       ▼\n44: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n45: │                   Runtime Layer                             │\n46: │  PublishRuntime │ InvokeRuntime │ StatusRuntime            │\n47: │         │              │               │                    │\n48: │         └──────────────┴───────────────┘                    │\n49: │                        │                                    │\n50: │                        ▼                                    │\n51: │              provider: \"agentcube\" | \"k8s\"                  │\n52: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n53:                         │\n54:           ┌─────────────┴─────────────┐\n55:           ▼                           ▼\n56: ┌───────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────┐\n57: │ KubernetesProvider│     │ AgentCubeProvider │\n58: │                   │     │                   │\n59: │ • Deployment      │     │ • AgentRuntime CR │\n60: │ • NodePort Service│     │ • CRD v1alpha1    │\n61: │ • wait_for_ready  │     │ • session mgmt    │\n62: └───────────────────┘     └───────────────────┘\n63:           │                           │\n64:           └───────────┬───────────────┘\n65:                       ▼\n66:             Kubernetes API Server\n67:                       │\n68:           ┌───────────┴───────────┐\n69:           ▼                       ▼\n70:    ┌─────────────┐      ┌─────────────────┐\n71:    │ Deployment  │      │ AgentRuntime CR │\n72:    │ + Service   │      │ (Operator)      │\n73:    └─────────────┘      └─────────────────┘\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ## Implementation Details\n77: \n78: ### 1. KubernetesProvider (`k8s_provider.py`)\n79: \n80: Standard Kubernetes deployment using `kubernetes` Python client:\n81: \n82: ```python\n83: class KubernetesProvider:\n84:     def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None)\n85:     def deploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port, entrypoint, replicas, node_port, env_vars) -> Dict\n86:     def get_agent_status(agent_name) -> Dict\n87:     def delete_agent(agent_name) -> Dict\n88:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120) -> None\n89: ```\n90: \n91: **Deployment Strategy:**\n92: - Creates `apps/v1` Deployment with configurable replicas\n93: - Creates `v1` Service of type NodePort (range 30000-32767)\n94: - Uses `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()` for local development\n95: - Names sanitized to DNS-compliant format (lowercase, hyphens only)\n96: \n97: ### 2. AgentCubeProvider (`agentcube_provider.py`)\n98: \n99: Custom Resource deployment for AgentCube operator:\n100: \n101: ```python\n102: class AgentCubeProvider:\n103:     def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None)\n104:     def deploy_agent_runtime(agent_name, image_url, port, entrypoint, env_vars, workload_manager_url, router_url, readiness_probe_path, readiness_probe_port) -> Dict\n105:     def get_agent_runtime(name, namespace) -> Optional[Dict]\n106: ```\n107: \n108: **CRD API:**\n109: - Group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n110: - Version: `v1alpha1`\n111: - Plural: `agentruntimes`\n112: \n113: **CR Spec Fields:**\n114: | Field | Source |\n115: |-------|--------|\n116: | `image` | `image_url` |\n117: | `entrypoint` | `entrypoint` |\n118: | `port` | `port` |\n119: | `env` | `env_vars` + WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL + ROUTER_URL |\n120: | `sessionTimeout` | `\"15m\"` |\n121: | `maxSessionDuration` | `\"8h\"` |\n122: | `readinessProbe` | From metadata or defaults |\n123: | `imagePullSecrets` | `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]` |\n124: \n125: ### 3. Provider Selection Logic\n126: \n127: **Publish Command (`--provider` flag):**\n128: \n129: | Provider | Behavior |\n130: |----------|----------|\n131: | `k8s` | `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` → `wait_for_deployment_ready()` |\n132: | `agentcube` | `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` |\n133: \n134: **Status Command:**\n135: \n136: | Provider | Status Source |\n137: |----------|---------------|\n138: | `k8s` | Deployment status + Service NodePort |\n139: | `agentcube` | AgentRuntime CR `.status` field |\n140: \n141: **Invoke Command:**\n142: \n143: | Provider | Endpoint Pattern |\n144: |----------|------------------|\n145: | `k8s` | `http://localhost:{node_port}` (direct) |\n146: | `agentcube` | `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/` |\n147: \n148: ### 4. Metadata Extensions\n149: \n150: New fields in `AgentMetadata`:\n151: \n152: | Field | Type | Description |\n153: |-------|------|-------------|\n154: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | URL for Workload Manager (AgentCube CR) |\n155: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | URL for Router (AgentCube CR) |\n156: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | Health check path |\n157: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | Health check port |\n158: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | Agent ID from AgentCube |\n159: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session ID for invocation |\n160: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict]` | Deployment metadata |\n161: \n162: ### 5. CLI Command Updates\n163: \n164: **`publish` command:**\n165: ```python\n166: --provider: str = \"agentcube\"  # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\"\n167: --node-port: Optional[int] = None  # For k8s provider (30000-32767)\n168: --replicas: Optional[int] = None   # For k8s provider\n169: --namespace: Optional[str] = None\n170: ```\n171: \n172: **`invoke` command:**\n173: ```python\n174: --provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n175: --header: Optional[List[str]] = None  # Repeatable\n176: ```\n177: \n178: **`status` command:**\n179: ```python\n180: --provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ## Dependencies\n184: \n185: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n186: |---------|---------|---------|\n187: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | K8s client library (optional dep in `k8s` extra) |\n188: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata validation |\n189: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for invoke |\n190: \n191: ## Error Handling\n192: \n193: | Error | Provider | Message |\n194: |-------|----------|---------|\n195: | Missing router_url/workload_manager_url | agentcube | \"Both router_url and workload_manager_url required in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n196: | Deployment timeout | k8s | `TimeoutError` after 120s |\n197: | Invalid node_port | k8s | Must be 30000-32767 |\n198: | CRD not found | agentcube | Check AgentCube operator installation |\n199: \n200: ## Testing Strategy\n201: \n202: ### Unit Tests\n203: - Mock `kubernetes.client` for `KubernetesProvider`\n204: - Mock dynamic client for `AgentCubeProvider`\n205: - Test provider selection in `PublishRuntime`\n206: - Test endpoint routing in `InvokeRuntime`\n207: \n208: ### Integration Tests\n209: - Minikube/KIND cluster for k8s provider\n210: - Mocked AgentCube operator for agentcube provider\n211: - End-to-end: pack → build → publish → invoke → status\n212: \n213: ## Migration Path\n214: \n215: Existing users (provider not specified):\n216: 1. `publish` defaults to `agentcube` provider\n217: 2. Metadata fields `router_url` and `workload_manager_url` must be configured\n218: 3. Users wanting standard K8s should set `--provider k8s`\n219: \n220: ## Acceptance Criteria\n221: \n222: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s` creates Deployment + NodePort Service\n223: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider agentcube` creates AgentRuntime CR\n224: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube invoke --provider k8s` routes to NodePort endpoint\n225: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube invoke --provider agentcube` routes through Router\n226: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube status --provider k8s` shows Deployment pod status\n227: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube status --provider agentcube` shows CR status\n228: - [ ] NodePort range validation (30000-32767)\n229: - [ ] Missing agentcube config raises clear error\n230: - [ ] Namespace isolation works for both providers\n231: - [ ] All commands support `--verbose` for detailed logging\n232: \n233: ## Risks & Mitigations\n234: \n235: | Risk | Mitigation |\n236: |------|------------|\n237: | K8s client dependency size | Make `kubernetes` an optional extra (`pip install agentcube[k8s]`) |\n238: | CRD API drift | Pin to `v1alpha1` and document compatibility |\n239: | Deployment timeout on slow clusters | Configurable timeout (default 120s) |\n240: | Multiple kubeconfig contexts | Support `--kubeconfig` flag (future) |\n241: \n242: ## Timeline\n243: \n244: | Phase | Duration | Deliverables |\n245: |-------|----------|--------------|\n246: | Phase 1 | 2 days | `KubernetesProvider` implementation |\n247: | Phase 2 | 2 days | `AgentCubeProvider` implementation |\n248: | Phase 3 | 1 day | Provider selection in runtime classes |\n249: | Phase 4 | 1 day | CLI command updates and metadata fields |\n250: | Phase 5 | 2 days | Testing (unit + integration) |\n251: | Phase 6 | 1 day | Documentation and examples |\n252: \n253: **Total: ~9 days**\n254: \n255: ## References\n256: \n257: - `cli-toolkit/design.md` — CLI package structure\n258: - `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Command specifications\n259: - `deployment/client-go.md` — AgentRuntime CRD client (Go)\n260: - `python-sdk/design.md` — SDK client implementation\n\n(End of file - total 260 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement a dual-provider deployment system for the AgentCube CLI that enables AI agents to be deployed to either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service) or the AgentCube custom resource (AgentRuntime CR). This feature provides users with flexibility in deployment targets while maintaining a consistent CLI experience.\n\n## Motivation\n\nUsers have different infrastructure setups:\n- **Standard Kubernetes**: Teams with existing K8s clusters who want to deploy agents as standard Deployments and NodePort Services\n- **AgentCube CRD**: Teams using the AgentCube operator (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh) who benefit from specialized CRD features like session management, workload manager integration, and router-based invocation\n\nSupporting both deployment targets from a single CLI tool reduces operational complexity and enables gradual adoption of AgentCube-specific features.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775879062000,"end":1775879062017}}}}
