{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879094178,"sessionID":"ses_2855cccfcffeKWiqLygEoViRUd","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa47f2a001HRcp2RHTl5v56Q","messageID":"msg_d7aa402380013fAVy1zajnO1Sn","sessionID":"ses_2855cccfcffeKWiqLygEoViRUd","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-86c16b9652d44408b2aa5a66b5c9dfd3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Purpose\n\nProvide a Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) enabling users to:\n1. Create and manage Code Interpreter sessions through the Workload Manager control plane\n2. Execute code and manage files via the Router data plane\n3. Invoke AgentRuntime workloads through the Router\n\nThis SDK abstracts HTTP communication with the AgentCube backend, offering a clean Pythonic API for session lifecycle, code execution, and file operations.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n**Package Structure:**\n- `agentcube/__init__.py` — Public exports (`CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`)\n- `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` — High-level `CodeInterpreterClient` with context manager support\n- `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` — High-level `AgentRuntimeClient` for agent invocations\n- `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` — `ControlPlaneClient` for session CRUD\n- `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — Code execution and file operations\n- `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — Agent runtime invocations\n- `agentcube/exceptions.py` — Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`)\n- `agentcube/utils/http.py` — HTTP session factory with connection pooling\n- `agentcube/utils/utils.py` — Token file reading utility\n- `agentcube/utils/log.py` — Logger factory\n\n**Features:**\n- Context manager lifecycle (`__enter__`/`__exit__`) for automatic cleanup\n- Session reuse via `session_id` parameter\n- Environment variable fallbacks (`ROUTER_URL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n- Kubernetes service account token auto-detection\n- Command execution with non-zero exit code handling\n- Python code execution via temp file + `python3` command\n- File operations: write, upload, download, list\n- Connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter`\n\n**HTTP Contracts:**\n- Control plane: `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}`\n- Data plane (Code Interpreter): `api/execute`, `api/files` (CRUD + multipart upload)\n- Data plane (Agent Runtime): `GET/POST` on invocation base URL with session header\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Async/await support (synchronous `requests`-based only)\n- Retry logic beyond HTTP adapter defaults\n- Custom authentication beyond Bearer token\n- Streaming file uploads/downloads beyond current design\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n**Runtime:**\n- `requests` — HTTP client\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` — JWT handling (Router integration)\n- `cryptography` — Cryptographic support\n\n**Build:**\n- Python >= 3.10\n- `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`\n\n### Affected Components\n\n| Component | Impact |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Workload Manager | Consumers via `ControlPlaneClient` |\n| Router | Consumers via data plane clients |\n| Code Interpreter | Primary integration target |\n| Agent Runtime | Secondary integration target |\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|------------|\n| Breaking API changes | Medium | Version via semver; deprecation policy |\n| Router URL misconfiguration | Medium | Clear error messages; environment fallbacks |\n| Session leak on exception | Low | Context manager ensures cleanup |\n| Timeout misalignment with PicoD | Low | Buffer +2s on read timeout |\n\n### Testing Strategy\n\n- Unit tests for client construction, URL resolution, timeout handling\n- Integration tests against mock HTTP servers\n- E2E tests against real Workload Manager and Router (scripts/e2e_picod_test.py)\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Async-first SDK (aiohttp)\n\n**Pros:**\n- Better suited for high-concurrency workloads\n- Native async/await patterns\n\n**Cons:**\n- Increased complexity for simple use cases\n- Requires async runtime (event loop)\n- `requests` ecosystem more mature for synchronous use\n\n**Decision:** Start synchronous; async can be added later via separate async clients.\n\n### 2. Single Configuration Class\n\n**Pros:**\n- Centralized defaults\n- Easier to pass around\n\n**Cons:**\n- Different clients have different required/configurable parameters\n- Less discoverable than constructor parameters\n- Inline defaults more explicit\n\n**Decision:** Distributed defaults per client; aligns with Python SDK conventions (e.g., boto3).\n\n### 3. Retry/Resilience Layer (tenacity, resilience4j-like)\n\n**Pros:**\n- Automatic retry on transient failures\n- Circuit breaker patterns\n\n**Cons:**\n- Adds dependency weight\n- Retry semantics depend on operation (idempotent vs not)\n- Can mask underlying issues\n\n**Decision:** Rely on `HTTPAdapter` connection pooling; users can wrap with retry if needed.\n\n### 4. Protobuf/Code-generated Clients\n\n**Pros:**\n- Type safety from OpenAPI/gRPC specs\n- Auto-generated client code\n\n**Cons:**\n- Adds build complexity\n- AgentCube APIs are REST/JSON, not gRPC\n- Current API surface small enough for manual clients\n\n**Decision:** Manual implementation; consider generation if API surface grows significantly.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775879094152,"end":1775879094176}}}}
